2. Data Cleaning¶

Let's now conduct some data cleaning steps.

We've seen that there are no missing values in the dataset. We've also seen that variables are in the correct format, except symboling, which should rather be a categorical variable (so that dummy variable are created for the categories).

Note that it can be used in the model as a numeric variable also.

There are total of 19 variables having missing vales and needs to be treated, either by deleting the columns or by imputing the values with some meaningful values.

  • PoolQC: - Removed becuase 99% missing values and even if it is meaningful it would be skewed

  • MiscFeature: Removed becuase 96% missing values and even if it is meaningful it would be skewed

  • Alley: Removed becuase 93% missing values and even if it is meaningful it would be skewed

  • Fence: Removed becuase 80% missing values and even if it is meaningful it would be skewed

  • FireplaceQu: Removed because 48% missing values and even if it is meaningful it would be skewed

  • LotFrontage: Imputed with median value

  • GarageCond: Label Encoding but used Replace method and defined the levels, 0 being poor and 5 being excellent

  • GarageType: Filled the missing values with "No_Garage" and then did One hot encoding

  • GarageYrBlt: Deleted the column as it was not possible to impute the year column and there were 81 missing values hence could not delete the rows as well

  • GarageFinish: Label Encoding but used Replace method and defined the levels

  • GarageQual: Label Encoding but used Replace method and defined the levels, 0 being poor and 5 being excellent

  • BsmtExposure: Label Encoding but used Replace method and defined the levels

  • BsmtFinType2: Label Encoding but used Replace method and defined the levels

  • BsmtFinType1: Label Encoding but used Replace method and defined the levels

  • BsmtCond: Label Encoding but used Replace method and defined the levels

  • BsmtQual: Label Encoding but used Replace method and defined the levels

  • MasVnrArea: Imputed with Median

  • MasVnrType: Droped the rows as there were only 8 missing values in the column

  • Electrical: Droped the rows as there was only 1 missing value in the column

# Dropping columns having highly skewed data, columns are: PoolQC, MiscFeature, Alley, Fence

# Treating all the above columns identified as missing value columns

lassoreidge_data["GarageType"] = lassoreidge_data["GarageType"].fillna("No_Gar")

lassoreidge_data["GarageFinish"].replace({"Fin": 3, "RFn": 2, "Unf": 1}, inplace=True)
lassoreidge_data["GarageFinish"] = lassoreidge_data["GarageFinish"].fillna(0)

lassoreidge_data["GarageQual"].replace({"Po": 1, "Fa": 2, "TA": 3, "Gd": 4, "Ex": 5}, inplace=True)
lassoreidge_data["GarageQual"] = lassoreidge_data["GarageQual"].fillna(0)

lassoreidge_data["BsmtExposure"].replace({"No": 1, "Mn": 2, "Av": 3, "Gd": 4}, inplace=True)
lassoreidge_data["BsmtExposure"] = lassoreidge_data["BsmtExposure"].fillna(0)

lassoreidge_data["BsmtFinType2"].replace({"Unf": 1, "LwQ": 2, "Rec": 3, "BLQ": 4, "ALQ": 5, "GLQ": 6}, inplace=True)
lassoreidge_data["BsmtFinType2"] = lassoreidge_data["BsmtFinType2"].fillna(0)

lassoreidge_data["BsmtFinType1"].replace({"Unf": 1, "LwQ": 2, "Rec": 3, "BLQ": 4, "ALQ": 5, "GLQ": 6}, inplace=True)
lassoreidge_data["BsmtFinType1"] = lassoreidge_data["BsmtFinType1"].fillna(0)

lassoreidge_data["BsmtCond"].replace({"Po": 1, "Fa": 2, "TA": 3, "Gd": 4, "Ex": 5}, inplace=True)
lassoreidge_data["BsmtCond"] = lassoreidge_data["BsmtCond"].fillna(0)

lassoreidge_data["BsmtQual"].replace({"Po": 1, "Fa": 2, "TA": 3, "Gd": 4, "Ex": 5}, inplace=True)
lassoreidge_data["BsmtQual"] = lassoreidge_data["BsmtQual"].fillna(0)

lassoreidge_data["MasVnrArea"] = lassoreidge_data["MasVnrArea"].fillna(lassoreidge_data["MasVnrArea"].median())

lassoreidge_data = lassoreidge_data.dropna()
